  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="eyebrow" data-i18n="cc.eyebrow3">On the roadmap</p>
        <h2 data-i18n="cc.h3">The working count cycle.</h2>
        <p data-i18n="cc.p5">
          Turning the scaffold into an operable function: generating tasks, capturing counts without
          bias, resolving variances and giving operators a UI.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-3">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-head"><div class="tag" data-i18n="cc.tag4">Tasks</div><span class="pill pill-roadmap" data-i18n="cc.pill5">Roadmap</span></div>
          <h3 data-i18n="cc.h9">Counting tasks</h3>
          <p data-i18n="cc.p6">Planned: generating and dispatching counting tasks — by location, by velocity class or on a cycle — from the COUNT order. Not yet implemented.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-head"><div class="tag" data-i18n="cc.tag5">Count modes</div><span class="pill pill-roadmap" data-i18n="cc.pill6">Roadmap</span></div>
          <h3 data-i18n="cc.h10">Blind &amp; variance counts</h3>
          <p data-i18n="cc.p7">Planned: blind counts that hide the expected quantity, plus variance counts that re-count only where the first pass disagreed. Designed for, not yet built.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-head"><div class="tag" data-i18n="cc.tag6">Reconciliation</div><span class="pill pill-roadmap" data-i18n="cc.pill7">Roadmap</span></div>
          <h3 data-i18n="cc.h11">Resolve &amp; adjust</h3>
          <p data-i18n="cc.p8">Planned: reconciliation that compares counted vs recorded, posts a StockAdjusted event within tolerance and escalates the rest. Not yet implemented.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-head"><div class="tag" data-i18n="cc.tag7">UI</div><span class="pill pill-roadmap" data-i18n="cc.pill8">Roadmap</span></div>
          <h3 data-i18n="cc.h12">Operator &amp; review screens</h3>
          <p data-i18n="cc.p9">Planned: the count UI for operators to enter counts and for supervisors to review variances and approve adjustments. Designed, not yet built.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

